      </Button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="accessibility">Accessibility</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Type attribute</strong>: Specify the appropriate type (button/submit/reset)</li>
    <li><strong>ariaLabel</strong>: Required for icon-only buttons</li>
    <li><strong>disabled</strong>: Disables the button and makes it inaccessible</li>
    <li><strong>Visible focus</strong>: Clear focus states on all variants</li>
    <li><strong>Contrast</strong>: Meets WCAG AA ratios</li>
  </ul>

  <Code
    lang="astro"
    code={`<ButtonComponent 
  icon={{ name: 'mdi:close' }}
  ariaLabel="Close window"
/>`}
  />

  <h2 id="best-practices">Best Practices</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Use <code class="inline-code">type="submit"</code> for form submission buttons</li>
    <li>Always provide <code class="inline-code">ariaLabel</code> for buttons without text</li>
    <li>Use colors consistently (primary for main action, etc.)</li>
    <li>Avoid too many icons, use sparingly</li>
    <li>Keep the same variant throughout the interface</li>
    <li>Disable buttons rather than hiding them during actions</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="css">CSS Customization</h2>

  <p>
    The component uses CSS tokens defined in the design system. 
    Styles are defined in <code class="inline-code">src/styles/components/</code> for each variant.
  </p>

  <h3>CSS Variables Used</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><code class="inline-code">--button-padding-y</code></li>
    <li><code class="inline-code">--button-padding-x</code></li>
    <li><code class="inline-code">--button-border-radius</code></li>
    <li><code class="inline-code">--button-font-size</code></li>
    <li><code class="inline-code">--button-primary-bg</code></li>
    <li><code class="inline-code">--button-primary-color</code></li>
    <li>And more...</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Comparison with Link</h2>

  <p>
    The <code class="inline-code">Button</code> component is similar to <code class="inline-code">Link</code> 
    but always rendered as a <code class="inline-code">&lt;button&gt;</code> element. 
    Use <code class="inline-code">Link</code> with <code class="inline-code">style="button"</code> 
    for buttons that are actually navigation links.
  </p>

  <div class="comparison-table">
    <Table striped>
      <TableHeader>
        <TableRow>
          <TableHead>Use Case</TableHead>
          <TableHead>Component to Use</TableHead>
        </TableRow>
      </TableHeader>
      <TableBody>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>Submit a form</TableCell>
          <TableCell><code class="inline-code">Button type="submit"</code></TableCell>
        </TableRow>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>JavaScript action</TableCell>
          <TableCell><code class="inline-code">Button</code></TableCell>
        </TableRow>
        <TableRow>
